# cursor-team — Project Conventions

## This Project

Cloud-based AI team memory backend for Cursor IDE. Express 5 server exposing MCP tools for memory, projects, playbook, and team bootstrap. Clerk-protected dashboard. Prisma with pgvector for semantic search.

## Tech Stack

TypeScript (ES2022), Express 5, Prisma, PostgreSQL + pgvector, Clerk, @modelcontextprotocol/sdk, OpenAI, Zod 4, Node >= 20.

## Code Style

- All inputs validated with Zod before processing
- Async/await with proper error handling on every async operation
- No `any` without explicit justification
- Prisma client imported from `src/db.ts` (singleton)
- Keep route handlers thin — business logic in dedicated functions
- MCP tool handlers follow consistent input validation → logic → response pattern

## File Organization

- `src/mcp/tools/` — one file per MCP tool domain (memory, project, playbook, bootstrap)
- `src/dashboard/` — Clerk-protected web UI routes and rendering
- `src/types.ts` — shared constants (team members, memory types)
- `prisma/schema.prisma` — single source of truth for data models

## Database

- Prisma is the ORM — never write raw SQL unless pgvector requires it
- pgvector embeddings are 1536-dimensional (OpenAI text-embedding-3-small)
- Avoid N+1 queries — use `include` or batch operations
- Run `npx prisma db push` for dev, `npx prisma migrate` for production changes

## Security

- Never hardcode secrets — use environment variables
- Clerk middleware on all dashboard routes
- Bearer token auth on MCP endpoint
- Validate all external inputs with Zod

